here are the main file system options for external SSDs on macOS:
APFS (Apple File System)
Best for macOS
Very efficient
Optimized for SSDs
Supports encryption
LIMITATION: Limited compatibility with Windows/Linux
HFS+ (Mac OS Extended)
Traditional Apple format
Works well with older Mac systems
LIMITATION: Same Windows/Linux compatibility issues as APFS
FAT32
Universal compatibility
LIMITATIONS:
4GB max file size
No files over 4GB
Not efficient for large drives
exFAT
